From: Yifei Sun <ysun@hey.com>
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] drm/vc4: register CEC adapter after audio_init to avoid probe loop

vc4_hdmi_audio_init() calls devm_snd_dmaengine_pcm_register(), which
can return -EPROBE_DEFER on platforms where the audio DMA engine
referenced by the 'dmas' DT property is not yet bound -- notably
Raspberry Pi 5 / BCM2712, where the RP1 DMA path is not yet supported
by mainline.

vc4_hdmi_cec_register() registers a CEC adapter as a child of the HDMI
platform device. Per Documentation/driver-api/driver-model/driver.rst,
adding a child device before returning -EPROBE_DEFER causes the driver
core to re-probe the parent. Each re-probe re-registers the CEC adapter
(creating a new rc-cec input device per iteration), saturating a CPU
and effectively locking the kernel within seconds.

Reorder vc4_hdmi_bind() so vc4_hdmi_audio_init() runs first, ensuring
that a deferring audio_init returns to the driver core before the CEC
adapter is added. This is the CEC-side counterpart to commit
c0317ad44f45 ("drm/vc4: fix infinite EPROBE_DEFER loop"), which
addressed the audio-side child-device registration. Note that this
patch must be applied on top of the duplicate-audio-init removal;
without that, the connector_init call still adds a child device
before audio_init defers and the loop persists.

On hardware where audio_init defers indefinitely (Pi 5 + mainline
today), CEC will not register either. This is a strict improvement
over the current state, where the system locks up within seconds of
CEC's first registration.

Fixes: cf207ea2c39d ("drm/vc4: hdmi: switch to generic CEC helpers")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Yifei Sun <ysun@hey.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_hdmi.c
@@ -3327,11 +3327,11 @@ static int vc4_hdmi_bind(struct device *dev, struct device *master, void *data)
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_put_runtime_pm;

-	ret = vc4_hdmi_cec_register(vc4_hdmi);
+	ret = vc4_hdmi_audio_init(vc4_hdmi);
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_put_runtime_pm;

-	ret = vc4_hdmi_audio_init(vc4_hdmi);
+	ret = vc4_hdmi_cec_register(vc4_hdmi);
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_put_runtime_pm;

